Description:
This brilliant, multicolored crop radiates hope for the future.

※Only for use in Omicron society quests.
※Not included in the gathering log.
Name: Karellian Prismatic Wheat

Description:
No one likes to say its name and no one wants to eat it. Leave this plant alone for gods' sake.

※Only for use in Omicron society quests.
※Not included in the gathering log.
Name: Puantplant

Description:
A sample of seaweed scientifically proven to be too good for this universe.

※Only for use in Omicron society quests.
※Not included in the gathering log.
Name: Supremest Kelp

Description:
Lichen lickerous to the likes of little Miw Miisv.

※Only for use in Omicron society quests.
※Not included in the gathering log.
Name: Softmoss

Description:
Wood as soft as the delicate fluttering of a baby Miw Miisv.

※Only for use in Omicron society quests.
※Not included in the gathering log.
Name: Supple Cosmowood

Description:
A beautiful, radiant flower that may serve as a beacon of hope for dragons residing in Reah Tahra.

※Only for use in Omicron society quests.
※Not included in the gathering log.
Name: Lucent Flower

Description:
Not the other kind.

※Only for use in Omicron society quests.
※Not included in the gathering log.
Name: True Dragon Fruit

Description:
Though the soft thistledown of this plant could, in theory, be used to provide a bed for dragons, the sheer amount that would be required is surely unsustainable.

※Only for use in Omicron society quests.
※Not included in the gathering log.
Name: Cotton-like Plant

Description:
This plant has medicinal properties that, when mixed with the appropriate ingredients, may create a mixture capable of producing fertile soil.

※Only for use in Omicron society quests.
※Not included in the gathering log.
Name: Elysian Herb

Description:
A stringy seaweed theoretically capable of cleaning the interdental spaces of a dragon's mouth─assuming one were brave enough to climb inside of it.

※Only for use in Omicron society quests.
※Not included in the gathering log.
Name: Fibrous Kelp

Description:
So moist it couldn't possibly be less than fresh!

※Only for use in Omicron society quests.
※Not included in the fish guide.
Name: Soggy Alien Kelp

Description:
This fish still smells of the sea, even after all this time. Or perhaps it was the sea that smelled of fish... Yes, definitely the second one.

※Only for use in Omicron society quests.
※Not included in the fish guide.
Name: Stellar Herring

Description:
With any luck, this inordinately unsupple fish can at least be boiled for stock without releasing toxic fumes.

※Only for use in Omicron society quests.
※Not included in the fish guide.
Name: Meteoric Bonito

Description:
The nigh-luminous green of this wavekin's scales is as beautiful as the peaks of the Dragonstar─assuming the beholder's eye belongs to a dragon, of course.

※Only for use in Omicron society quests.
※Not included in the fish guide.
Name: Copperscale

Description:
Of the universe's many unfortunate fish, this is perhaps the worst off.

※Only for use in Omicron society quests.
※Not included in the fish guide.
Name: Methane Puffer

Description:
A species of fish only found out amongst the cosmos─which may be for the best. To be used in the synthesis of low-grade herbicide.

※Only for use in Omicron society quests.
※Not included in the fish guide.
Name: Chemically Rich Fish

Description:
A sample of wildlife which will be tested to determine the purity of water from the wellspring of regret.

※Only for use in Omicron society quests.
※Not included in the fish guide.
Name: Wildlife Sample

Description:
Hardly a catch worth noting in its own environment, this unremarkable fish may be the key to enriching Elysian soil.

※Only for use in Omicron society quests.
※Not included in the fish guide.
Name: Nondescript Fish

Description:
The salty tang of dried seaweed is favored by coffee connoisseurs of discerning tastes.

※Only for use in Omicron society quests.
※Not included in the fish guide.
Name: Fresh Seaweed

Description:
A soft-bodied mollusk found in the ocean waters of Elysion.

※Only for use in Omicron society quests.
※Not included in the fish guide.
Name: Elysian Nudibranch

Description:
This fish is highly valued for the viscous film secreted over its scales that is said to have shock-absorbing properties.

※Only for use in Omicron society quests.
※Not included in the fish guide.
Name: Sticky Fingers

Description:
A nutrient-dense saltwater fish often used in aquaculture.

※Only for use in Omicron society quests.
※Not included in the fish guide.
Name: Elysian Stickleback

Description:
Despite the myriad flavors to be found in the sea, this fish chose to be salty.

※Only for use in Omicron society quests.
※Not included in the fish guide.
Name: Saltwater Fish

Description:
Despite its sickly green color, this saltwater fish is considered a delicacy among Karellians, proving even hideous things can be tasty on the inside.

※Only for use in Omicron society quests.
※Not included in the fish guide.
Name: Seaweed Snapper

Description:
An aquatic organism that truly embodies the maxim “be yourself.”

※Only for use in Omicron society quests.
※Not included in the fish guide.
Name: Karellian Fishy Fish

Description:
This creature transcends the concept of “fish,” its chilling gaze daring only the most foolish to consume its flesh.

※Only for use in Omicron society quests.
※Not included in the fish guide.
Name: Paraichthyoid

Description:
A magnificent shelled organism to be envied and admired.

※Only for use in Omicron society quests.
※Not included in the fish guide.
Name: Supremest Crustacean

Description:
These crayfish are named both for their miniature appearance and the delightful paste their creamed bodies make for infant Miw Miisv.

※Only for use in Omicron society quests.
※Not included in the fish guide.
Name: Babycray

Description:
A smooth and powdery calcareous deposit perfect for corporeal snuggling.

※Only for use in Omicron society quests.
※Not included in the fish guide.
Name: Silky Cosmocoral

Description:
This crimson-finned fish is sure to provide some vibrancy to the murky waters of Reah Tahra.

※Only for use in Omicron society quests.
※Not included in the fish guide.
Name: Chromatic Fish

Description:
Research indicates dragons cannot resist the crunchy texture of this bony fish.

※Only for use in Omicron society quests.
※Not included in the fish guide.
Name: Dragon's Delight

Description:
Though you cannot be certain how this otherworldly clump of algae will prove beneficial to dragons, it's the thought that counts.

※Only for use in Omicron society quests.
※Not included in the fish guide.
Name: Astral Algae

Description:
An entirely alien species of fish containing nutrients that may or may not improve the health of soil.

※Only for use in Omicron society quests.
※Not included in the fish guide.
Name: Weird Fish

Description:
This still very much alive and wriggling sponge can be scrubbed against a dragon's fangs for a proper cleaning, but probably shouldn't be for the sake of both parties involved.

※Only for use in Omicron society quests.
※Not included in the fish guide.
Name: Cosmic Sponge
